# Track & Field Central

Track & Field Central is a responsive multi-page website built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript that showcases my personal track & field journey while simulating a real-world athletic records and submission platform.

The project combines personal athletic experiences with interactive web development concepts including navigation systems, searchable records databases, categorized event organization, and validated form submissions.

**Currently working towards full deployment by integrating the website with a live hosting environment to support a functional form
## Features

### Home Page
- Personal track & field biography
- Athletic progression from cross country to collegiate decathlon training
- Favorite events and personal records
- Track & field historical content
- Responsive navigation bar and layout
- Embedded images and external resources

### Records Page
- Searchable track & field records database
- Categorized event groupings:
  - Sprints
  - Hurdles
  - Mid Distance
  - Long Distance
  - Throwing Events
  - Jumping Events
  - Multi-Events
- Dynamic filtering and event grouping
- Structured athlete performance tables
- Responsive data presentation

### Add Yours Page
- Interactive PR submission form
- Event selection using categorized dropdown menus
- Gender selection and athlete information input
- Validation for required fields
- Notes and date tracking support
- Structured user input system

## Technologies Used
- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript

## Skills Demonstrated
- Responsive web design
- Multi-page website architecture
- DOM manipulation
- Form validation
- Dynamic filtering and searching
- Data organization and presentation
- User interface design
- Semantic HTML structure

## Purpose
This project was created as a final web development project to demonstrate front-end development skills while combining a personal passion for track & field with interactive website functionality.

